Hello. Angel?

03:28.766 --> 03:32.141
I'd like to make an appointment.

03:54.725 --> 03:56.099
Hey.

03:56.100 --> 03:57.349
I'm Angel.

03:57.350 --> 03:59.641
I'm Nora. Come on in.

04:09.766 --> 04:11.724
Have a seat.

04:11.725 --> 04:13.349
Can I get you
something to drink?

04:13.350 --> 04:16.765
No. Thanks.
I'm good.

04:16.766 --> 04:18.265
Nice mattress.

04:18.266 --> 04:19.932
That for us?

04:19.933 --> 04:21.391
That's for me.

04:22.850 --> 04:24.725
You want me to watch you?

04:27.266 --> 04:29.640
No, I want you to shoot me.

04:39.225 --> 04:40.557
No way.
No fuckin' way.

04:40.558 --> 04:42.224
Just...

04:42.225 --> 04:44.974
$2,000 for two seconds.

04:44.975 --> 04:47.182
Your ad specifically said,

04:47.183 --> 04:49.599
"Nothing is
forbidden."

04:49.600 --> 04:52.182
Lady, I fuck people.
I don't kill them.

04:52.183 --> 04:55.100
If I wanted to die,
I wouldn't need you.

05:00.225 --> 05:01.766
I'll talk you through it.

05:15.350 --> 05:17.850
It's Kevlar.

05:21.058 --> 05:23.974
All you have to do...

05:23.975 --> 05:25.932
is aim right here.

05:25.933 --> 05:27.683
Just above the stomach,
just below my heart.

05:31.433 --> 05:33.516
You've done this before?

05:34.016 --> 05:37.015
Yes.

05:37.016 --> 05:40.224
Why didn't you
just get the person
that shot you last time?

05:40.225 --> 05:41.766
She said she wouldn't
do it again.

05:47.600 --> 05:48.683
I need another thousand.

05:51.558 --> 05:53.058
OK.

06:05.016 --> 06:08.516
Go ahead.

06:26.975 --> 06:28.933
What if I miss?

06:30.475 --> 06:32.558
You won't.

06:40.808 --> 06:43.225
What happened to you?

06:57.225 --> 06:59.640
Hold it up.
Two hands.

06:59.641 --> 07:01.307
All right?

07:01.308 --> 07:02.808
OK?

07:06.850 --> 07:08.474
Aim right here!

07:08.475 --> 07:11.890
Just pull the trigger, OK?

07:11.891 --> 07:14.474
On 3.

07:14.475 --> 07:16.349
1...

07:16.350 --> 07:18.307
2...

07:18.308 --> 07:19.433
3!

07:20.850 --> 07:21.850
Do it!
Just wait!

07:21.851 --> 07:23.515
Just do it!
I can't!

07:23.516 --> 07:24.141
Just do it!
I can't!

07:24.142 --> 07:26.516
Do it now!

09:17.600 --> 09:20.224
Nora Jamison Durst,

09:20.225 --> 09:22.057
you have provided the
appropriate documentation,

09:22.058 --> 09:26.182
certifying the respondents'
status as "Departed"?

09:26.183 --> 09:27.974
Yes, I have.

09:27.975 --> 09:29.807
And you wish to dissolve
the marriage between

09:29.808 --> 09:32.807
yourself, the plaintiff,
and the respondent,

09:32.808 --> 09:34.600
Douglas Isaac Durst?

09:36.100 --> 09:38.474
I do.

09:38.475 --> 09:40.974
And is there any matter
of custody or removal

09:40.975 --> 09:43.974
of children, here named
Jeremy and Erin,

09:43.975 --> 09:46.682
to be resolved
within this application?

09:46.683 --> 09:49.141
My children are also
Departed, Your Honor.

09:52.183 --> 09:54.058
I'm sorry to hear that.

09:56.891 --> 09:59.807
Should the departed
respondent return,

09:59.808 --> 10:01.515
this will remain binding.

10:01.516 --> 10:05.515
Do you still want to proceed?

10:05.516 --> 10:09.433
My husband was sleeping with
our kids' preschool teacher.

10:14.225 --> 10:16.515
Yes, I'd like to proceed.

10:16.516 --> 10:17.890
All right.

10:17.891 --> 10:20.640
The court hereby grants
a Judgment of Divorce.

10:20.641 --> 10:24.724
While you're here,
would you like

10:24.725 --> 10:27.224
to legally revert
to your maiden name?

10:27.225 --> 10:28.474
It's just another form...

10:28.475 --> 10:31.475
No, thank you.
I'd like to remain
Nora Durst.

10:39.141 --> 10:40.641
Hey.

10:41.100 --> 10:44.474
Hey.

10:44.475 --> 10:46.474
That's a traffic ticket,
I can get you out of it.

10:46.475 --> 10:48.057
Oh. Divorce.

10:48.058 --> 10:50.515
I just got myself out of it.

10:50.516 --> 10:52.515
Oh. Small world.

10:52.516 --> 10:54.474
Me, too.

10:54.475 --> 10:56.307
You're joking.

10:56.308 --> 10:59.807
No, I should have got
the hint when she joined
the Guilty Remnant.

11:04.516 --> 11:06.515
Oh, you're not joking.

11:06.516 --> 11:08.099
Oh, no.

11:08.100 --> 11:09.599
I don't know how to joke.

11:11.975 --> 11:14.390
Do you want to go to Miami?

11:14.391 --> 11:16.140
What?

11:16.141 --> 11:17.682
I was supposed to go
to this work conference
in Manhattan

11:17.683 --> 11:19.682
on Friday, but it's
gonna be terrible,

11:19.683 --> 11:22.683
and I was thinking
maybe Miami instead.

11:24.183 --> 11:26.765
Oh, uh...

11:26.766 --> 11:29.015
Oh, I live with
my daughter, so I...

11:29.016 --> 11:30.808
Oh, fuck your daughter.

11:33.391 --> 11:36.015
I'm sorry. That...

11:36.016 --> 11:38.557
I am so sorry.

11:38.558 --> 11:39.683
Look...

11:48.808 --> 11:50.390
Department of Sudden Departure.

11:50.391 --> 11:53.724
Hi, Tracy. Is he in?

11:53.725 --> 11:56.140
Yes, he is.
OK, thank you.

11:56.141 --> 11:57.641
Hey.

12:01.308 --> 12:04.724
Come in.

12:04.725 --> 12:08.224
Ma'am, the benefits
aren't determ...

12:08.225 --> 12:11.265
Right, but our office
has nothing to say about...

12:11.266 --> 12:13.474
Hello? Ma'am?

12:15.141 --> 12:17.974
I feel like I have
the same conversation
80 fuckin' times a day.

12:17.975 --> 12:19.015
I have no idea what you mean.

12:19.016 --> 12:21.557
Sit.

12:23.100 --> 12:27.140
So, uh, you ready
for your panel,
whatever, at DROP?

12:27.141 --> 12:29.140
Yes, sir.
They put me on Day Two,

12:29.141 --> 12:31.807
along with Rhode Island
and Connecticut.

12:31.808 --> 12:35.599
Just don't let them
bully you into taking
questions about the data.

12:35.600 --> 12:38.557
All right, they gave us
a pass last year, but they're
gonna want answers this time.

12:38.558 --> 12:39.765
"I'm sorry, Sir or Madam,
I'm not qualified

12:39.766 --> 12:42.974
"to analyze the data
from our questionnaires.

12:42.975 --> 12:45.974
I don't even have access
to it before it goes to our
statisticians in Annapolis."

12:45.975 --> 12:47.974
Oh, shit.

12:47.975 --> 12:49.557
Annapolis. Speaking of,

12:49.558 --> 12:52.640
what are you doing on 121?

12:52.641 --> 12:53.641
What?

12:53.642 --> 12:54.766
I just got this email.

12:57.225 --> 13:01.015
"Please inquire ID 42ECN
as to the manner

13:01.016 --> 13:03.640
by which he/she presents
Question 121."

13:03.641 --> 13:04.766
What are you doing?

13:08.891 --> 13:11.391
OK.

13:14.683 --> 13:17.265
I'm not doing anything.

13:17.266 --> 13:20.849
It says here you're
100% affirmative.

13:20.850 --> 13:24.390
Every single one
of your applicants
answers 121 "yes."

13:24.391 --> 13:27.224
Isn't that what we're
supposed to be looking
for, a pattern?

13:27.225 --> 13:29.432
Everyone else who ask
the questions get
plenty of "nos."

13:29.433 --> 13:32.224
It's only a pattern for you.

13:32.225 --> 13:36.099
Maybe you're, um...

13:36.100 --> 13:39.099
mentioning what happened to you,

13:39.100 --> 13:42.140
hmm, you know, before you roll,

13:42.141 --> 13:44.308
just to get people comfortable?

13:45.808 --> 13:47.641
I would never do that.

13:49.141 --> 13:51.765
OK. Sure.

13:51.766 --> 13:55.432
No, I know.
I'll talk to Annapolis.

13:55.433 --> 13:57.765
Mmm.

13:57.766 --> 14:00.016
Well, enjoy the conference, OK?

14:01.891 --> 14:02.891
Hey.

14:06.141 --> 14:08.515
When you took it,

14:08.516 --> 14:11.182
when they asked you 121,

14:11.183 --> 14:13.390
what'd you answer?

14:13.391 --> 14:16.765
I said yes, all 3 times.

14:21.683 --> 14:23.432
Hello.

14:23.433 --> 14:25.265
You've reached
the Durst residence.
Please leave a message.

14:25.266 --> 14:28.099
Hi, Nora.
It's Rick Carson.

14:28.100 --> 14:30.765
Just wanted to thank you again
for being a panelist

14:30.766 --> 14:34.182
at this year's
Departure-Related Occupations
and Practices conference.

14:34.183 --> 14:37.390
Your unique perspective is
really valuable to us.

14:37.391 --> 14:41.182
And a heads-up. We're expecting
a big crowd this year,
so register early.

14:41.183 --> 14:43.599
I'm really looking forward
to meeting you in person.

14:54.850 --> 14:55.850
Look in the Bible.

14:55.851 --> 14:57.557
Look right now.
Look today!

14:57.558 --> 15:00.349
They're poisoning us!

15:03.850 --> 15:05.725
Have you seen this?

15:12.308 --> 15:13.640
He's still here.

15:13.641 --> 15:15.265
He's hiding
in a basement in Sicily.

15:15.266 --> 15:17.224
Don't trust the Vatican.
The Pope is still here.

15:22.891 --> 15:25.224
Any fucking time now.

15:25.225 --> 15:26.849
Fuck you!

15:26.850 --> 15:27.683
Sons of bitches.

15:27.684 --> 15:30.516
Can't do this to us!

15:49.808 --> 15:51.765
Ms. Durst.

15:51.766 --> 15:54.015
You are staying
with us for two nights?

15:54.016 --> 15:55.599
Mm-hmm.

15:55.600 --> 15:57.890
So what's up with all
the people outside?

15:57.891 --> 16:00.099
There's a lot more
than last year.

16:00.100 --> 16:02.432
Well, you know, anything
about the Departure
for some people.

16:02.433 --> 16:03.682
Can't let it go.
Hmm.

16:03.683 --> 16:05.682
This is the hotel's
code of conduct.

16:05.683 --> 16:08.432
Please read carefully and sign.

16:08.433 --> 16:11.265
We had some issues
with your conference
last year.

16:11.266 --> 16:12.390
Really?

16:12.391 --> 16:13.016
Better cancel the kegger.

16:13.017 --> 16:15.225
Heh heh!

16:20.516 --> 16:22.307
Registration is
on the third floor.

16:22.308 --> 16:23.807
Enjoy your stay.

16:23.808 --> 16:25.683
Thank you.

16:28.016 --> 16:29.307
OK.

16:29.308 --> 16:32.057
There you go.

16:32.058 --> 16:33.682
Hi.

16:33.683 --> 16:35.682
Nora Durst.

16:35.683 --> 16:37.682
Durst. Great.

16:37.683 --> 16:39.432
Uh...

16:39.433 --> 16:42.725
Here's your welcome bag.
Let me look up your badge.

16:46.391 --> 16:48.390
Hey, you want
a good cry, read that.

16:48.391 --> 16:50.890
He lost 4 people on the 14th.

16:50.891 --> 16:52.890
That's terrible.

16:52.891 --> 16:55.099
Isn't it? Um...

16:55.100 --> 16:57.349
looks like somebody already
picked up your badge.

16:57.350 --> 16:59.890
What?
I just got here.

16:59.891 --> 17:03.057
Well, somebody must have
picked it up by mistake.

17:03.058 --> 17:04.640
No worries.

17:04.641 --> 17:07.265
This'll get you in
to all the events.

17:07.266 --> 17:10.265
Sorry for the confusion, OK?

17:10.266 --> 17:12.682
Next person? Hi.
Your name, please?

17:12.683 --> 17:14.016
Williams.

17:18.266 --> 17:21.515
'Scuse me. I'm sorry.
I need my badge.

17:21.516 --> 17:23.807
I... I'm a panelist
tomorrow.

17:23.808 --> 17:27.348
I work for the Department
of Sudden Departure
and I'm a legacy.

17:27.349 --> 17:29.515
I'm sorry for your loss.

17:29.516 --> 17:31.640
I'd like to give you
a legacy decal to go
on your guest badge,

17:31.641 --> 17:34.057
but we don't have any left.

17:34.058 --> 17:35.724
No, of course.
Thank you.

17:35.725 --> 17:37.724
But you understand
that if somebody
took my badge...

17:37.725 --> 17:39.515
Well, I'm sure it was
just an innocent mistake.

17:39.516 --> 17:41.557
Why don't you go
into the mixer?
Everyone is in there.

17:41.558 --> 17:43.350
I'm sure your badge
is in there, too.

17:44.600 --> 17:47.141
Yes.
Next person, please.

17:55.058 --> 17:57.890
They can
deny it all they want.
North Korea lost people.

17:57.891 --> 18:00.558
We can't ignore the possibility.

18:03.475 --> 18:07.099
Oh! God.
Hey there, easy...

18:07.100 --> 18:10.349
"Guest"?

18:10.350 --> 18:11.724
What's up? Marcus.

18:11.725 --> 18:14.349
I have the most
interesting job
at the conference.

18:14.350 --> 18:15.557
And I don't believe
in name tags.

18:15.558 --> 18:17.682
If you want to know
what I do, just ask me.

18:17.683 --> 18:19.015
It's a fucking
madhouse this year.

18:19.016 --> 18:23.515
You might want
to watch out for
Baldy over there.

18:23.516 --> 18:26.932
He's working the room,
asking people, "Do you really
want to feel this way?"

18:26.933 --> 18:29.307
It's a great fucking pitch.
I give him that.

18:29.308 --> 18:31.765
I mean, who the fuck
wants to feel this way?

18:31.766 --> 18:34.224
I have to go.
It was nice meeting you.

18:34.225 --> 18:35.807
Hey, hey, hey, Guest.

18:35.808 --> 18:39.807
So you're seriously not
gonna ask me what I do?

18:39.808 --> 18:41.724
OK, what do you do?

18:41.725 --> 18:45.140
You don't want
to know what I do.

18:45.141 --> 18:47.140
OK.

18:50.725 --> 18:56.099
We can't deny
the rising instances

18:56.100 --> 18:59.474
of Post-Departure
Delusion Disorder.

18:59.475 --> 19:02.432
Or some pundits have

19:02.433 --> 19:05.015
cheekily taken to calling it

19:05.016 --> 19:06.808
"The Prophet's Dilemma."

19:09.266 --> 19:11.557
For most of humankind's
existence,

19:11.558 --> 19:14.599
certain individuals
have come forth

19:14.600 --> 19:18.349
as self-professed interpreters

19:18.350 --> 19:20.640
of the world's mysteries.

19:20.641 --> 19:21.849
But what happens

19:21.850 --> 19:27.224
when those conversations
with God go wrong?

19:27.225 --> 19:30.849
Following a catastrophic
event or circumstance,

19:30.850 --> 19:34.890
let alone one that defies
scientific explanation,

19:34.891 --> 19:38.015
the incidence
of prophetic delusion

19:38.016 --> 19:39.599
rise dramatically.

19:39.600 --> 19:42.640
And this isn't
just megalomaniacs

19:42.641 --> 19:46.224
who make the news for a week.

19:46.225 --> 19:49.224
This is happening
to our friends,

19:49.225 --> 19:53.849
our neighbors, our own families.

19:53.850 --> 19:59.224
This belief that a higher power
is speaking to us,

19:59.225 --> 20:04.265
whether through dreams
or signs, even voices,

20:04.266 --> 20:07.265
is a powerful coping mechanism,

20:07.266 --> 20:10.640
and if left unchecked,

20:10.641 --> 20:13.557
it is a very dangerous one.

20:28.183 --> 20:30.183
Thank you, sir.

20:40.433 --> 20:43.350
I can wait as long as you want.

20:54.475 --> 20:57.558
I am so sorry.
I thought you were
somebody else.

20:59.016 --> 21:01.432
You don't remember me, do you?

21:01.433 --> 21:04.099
No.

21:04.100 --> 21:08.224
Last year, you called me
a heartless bitch at
the farewell party.

21:08.225 --> 21:10.599
I don't know...
no, that wasn't me.

21:10.600 --> 21:12.640
Yes, it was.
Your name is Nora.

21:12.641 --> 21:15.265
You lost your husband and kids.

21:16.475 --> 21:19.265
You work
for Linden-Bix?

21:19.266 --> 21:20.890
I do.

21:22.850 --> 21:24.849
You said my kids disappeared

21:24.850 --> 21:25.766
because I gave them
Frosted Flakes.

21:25.767 --> 21:29.474
No, I mentioned a correlation

21:29.475 --> 21:31.515
between eating cereals
high in sugar

21:31.516 --> 21:34.515
and pre-adolescent
Departures in a
cocktail conversation.

21:34.516 --> 21:38.307
And then you made me cry
in front of a roomful
of people.

21:38.308 --> 21:40.765
I am sorry.
Last year I didn't...

21:40.766 --> 21:42.640
I...

21:42.641 --> 21:45.600
I was having a really hard time.

21:47.308 --> 21:49.683
You're doing so much better now.

21:59.641 --> 22:01.599
May I have
your attention, please?

22:01.600 --> 22:05.140
The breakout session
of the Brandenburg Carousel
has been moved to Room 6-B.

22:05.141 --> 22:09.850
6-B in 10 minutes
for the Brandenburg
Carousel. Thank you.

22:15.766 --> 22:17.766
I'll take the next one.

22:34.433 --> 22:36.015
Holy shit! It's Guest!

22:36.016 --> 22:38.015
Oh, get in here.
We haven't seen you.

22:38.016 --> 22:40.015
You know, actually...
She's crazy, this one.

22:40.016 --> 22:41.057
I was just going.
No, no, you're not.

22:41.058 --> 22:43.057
You're going up
the elevator. Ha ha!

22:43.058 --> 22:44.224
This is wild.

22:44.225 --> 22:45.807
Get this, get this.

22:45.808 --> 22:48.224
I gave this young lady
my best "you don't
want to know,"

22:48.225 --> 22:51.390
and she still refused
to ask me what I do.

22:51.391 --> 22:53.015
Oh, I like her.
Well, guess what, Guest?
We got you now.

22:53.016 --> 22:56.932
You're coming up to
the hospitality suite
for drinks.

22:56.933 --> 22:58.613
Thanks, but I have
a panel tomorrow,
so I...

23:00.641 --> 23:03.390
Fuck, Marcus!
No, no, no, no.

23:03.391 --> 23:05.599
You have a choice, Guest.

23:05.600 --> 23:08.224
You can play by
the rules of this fucking
depressing conference

23:08.225 --> 23:12.307
like everybody else,
or you can go down
the rabbit hole with us.

23:12.308 --> 23:15.224
So what's it gonna be?

23:15.225 --> 23:16.890
You want to spend
the next two days
of your life dying,

23:16.891 --> 23:20.515
one panel at a time,
or do you want to live?

23:23.558 --> 23:26.057
Oh, ho, ho! Oh, yes!

23:26.058 --> 23:28.682
Oh, poor Patrick Johansen.

23:28.683 --> 23:31.765
It's a fuckin' tragedy,
what happened to him, yeah.

23:31.766 --> 23:34.307
Four! He lost 4.
Did you read the book?

23:34.308 --> 23:36.724
I try not to read
anything that comes
in a fuckin' tote.

23:36.725 --> 23:38.807
Leave that shit to the oranges.

23:38.808 --> 23:41.057
- What's an orange?
- The badges.

23:41.058 --> 23:42.140
You know,
some people have
the orange stickers?

23:42.141 --> 23:43.640
The legacies?

23:43.641 --> 23:46.224
Legacies, orphans, survivors.

23:46.225 --> 23:49.015
Whatever they want to be
called this year.
It's awful.

23:49.016 --> 23:50.682
It's a fucking tragedy.

23:50.683 --> 23:52.682
It's like I'm supposed
to treat them better
than anyone else?

23:52.683 --> 23:54.265
How many times am I
supposed to say
I'm sorry, right?

23:54.266 --> 23:57.765
Right, right.

23:59.641 --> 24:01.265
You pregnant, Guest?

24:01.266 --> 24:02.599
What?

24:02.600 --> 24:05.682
Any suicidal
thoughts, history
of heart problems?

24:05.683 --> 24:06.308
No.

24:06.309 --> 24:08.974
What is this?

24:08.975 --> 24:10.515
Don't worry.

