do this! I didn't do
anything wrong!

30:00.725 --> 30:04.682
I have... I have a panel
in a few hours!

30:04.683 --> 30:07.474
If we see you
on these premises again,
we're gonna call the police.

30:24.433 --> 30:25.933
Morning.

31:07.433 --> 31:09.682
Thanks for printing those out.

31:09.683 --> 31:12.390
Um, I lost my ID
at a conference.

31:12.391 --> 31:13.974
I have to get back
for a panel I'm on.

31:13.975 --> 31:17.683
I work for
the Department of
Sudden Departures.

31:23.225 --> 31:26.100
This is good.

31:50.225 --> 31:53.640
So, Nora Durst,
what are you doing
back in my hotel

31:53.641 --> 31:57.640
with a fake credential
and a gun?

31:57.641 --> 32:00.807
That's not for...
I forgot I had that with me.

32:00.808 --> 32:02.975
I am supposed to be
on a panel this morning.

32:05.058 --> 32:07.057
So, why did you throw a bottle

32:07.058 --> 32:08.265
at the mirror behind
the hotel bar?

32:08.266 --> 32:10.682
I wasn't in the bar.

32:10.683 --> 32:13.682
Someone is impersonating me.

32:13.683 --> 32:16.599
No offense,
but who would want
to pretend to be you?

32:16.600 --> 32:19.015
I don't know.
There are a lot
of sick people out there.

32:19.016 --> 32:22.640
Maybe somebody's doing it
for attention. I...

32:22.641 --> 32:25.640
My husband and two children
are... departed,

32:25.641 --> 32:27.766
and that sort of thing,
it gets a lot of sympathy.

32:31.308 --> 32:33.600
Jesus, your whole family?

32:34.350 --> 32:37.015
What are the odds?

32:37.016 --> 32:39.850
One in 128,000.

32:44.225 --> 32:46.224
OK, let's try this on for size.

32:46.225 --> 32:48.265
I know how these
conferences can be.

32:48.266 --> 32:51.224
Away from home, new people.

32:51.225 --> 32:53.599
So maybe things got out of hand,

32:53.600 --> 32:55.224
- one drink too many...
- No...

32:55.225 --> 32:56.599
No, no...
Listen to me.

32:56.600 --> 33:00.599
Maybe you did go
down to that bar

33:00.600 --> 33:01.849
and things got out of control.

33:01.850 --> 33:05.265
Maybe you've been
under a lot of stress

33:05.266 --> 33:08.599
and you just...

33:08.600 --> 33:10.265
lost your grip on things.

33:10.266 --> 33:13.265
Is that possible?

33:13.266 --> 33:15.640
No, that is not possible.

33:15.641 --> 33:16.849
Please, just...

33:16.850 --> 33:20.599
She is probably
on my panel right now.

33:20.600 --> 33:22.807
The other panelists
don't know me.

33:22.808 --> 33:26.015
She could walk onstage
with my badge and nobody
would stop her,

33:26.016 --> 33:28.433
so please!

33:33.391 --> 33:35.599
All right.

33:35.600 --> 33:37.974
If I walk you down
to that conference room

33:37.975 --> 33:40.557
and there's no one there
pretending to be you,

33:40.558 --> 33:44.640
then you leave this hotel
and I never see your face
again. Deal?

33:44.641 --> 33:46.141
Deal.

33:56.183 --> 33:58.182
I'm sorry. The session's
already started.

33:58.183 --> 33:59.849
We're just gonna be a minute.

33:59.850 --> 34:01.807
Next we have
Marquee Jackson
from Vermont.

34:01.808 --> 34:04.765
Beside him, we have
Olivia Livingstone

34:04.766 --> 34:06.765
from the Rhode Island
branch of the DSD,

34:06.766 --> 34:08.849
which has the highest
participation rate

34:08.850 --> 34:11.474
in the benefit program
in the country.

34:11.475 --> 34:14.474
Next, we have
Jonathan Van Meter,
also from Vermont,

34:14.475 --> 34:17.931
and beside him,
Nora Durst from New York.

34:17.933 --> 34:20.391
Mrs. Durst is also
a triple legacy.

34:21.891 --> 34:23.224
Well, fuck.

34:23.225 --> 34:26.264
I need two guys
to the Waterloo
Room right now.

34:26.266 --> 34:29.639
...Pritcher,
liaison with the Canadian
Departure Census,

34:29.641 --> 34:32.764
and he'll talk
about how they collect
their data up north.

34:32.766 --> 34:35.556
And finally, Daniel McCallum
from Connecticut.

34:35.558 --> 34:37.724
Daniel served on
the Review Committee...

34:37.725 --> 34:41.139
Excuse me!
I have a question.

34:41.141 --> 34:42.599
Uh, we haven't started
the panel yet...

34:42.600 --> 34:45.014
I have a question
for Nora Durst.

34:45.016 --> 34:47.014
We will open the floor
to questions...

34:47.016 --> 34:49.224
I am not Nora Durst.

34:51.808 --> 34:53.764
I have been watching you people

34:53.766 --> 34:57.182
for the last two days,
listening to you,

34:57.183 --> 34:59.557
and you are all blind.

34:59.558 --> 35:01.515
Puppets.

35:01.516 --> 35:03.932
Ma'am.
The Department
of the Sudden Departure

35:03.933 --> 35:06.640
is an elaborate smokescreen
to give the public

35:06.641 --> 35:07.183
the illusion of progress.
Ma'am, I'm sorry.

35:07.184 --> 35:09.349
Excuse me.

35:09.350 --> 35:11.515
Their questionnaires
are sent to incinerators

35:11.516 --> 35:12.849
outside of Tallahassee, Florida.

35:12.850 --> 35:15.140
Shut this off!
Their benefit payments

35:15.141 --> 35:16.932
are a way to silence us all.

35:16.933 --> 35:20.390
In 2005, the Israeli
Mossad was experimenting

35:20.391 --> 35:21.974
with a plasma ray
that could target

35:21.975 --> 35:25.724
all human matter and
leave almost no residue.

35:25.725 --> 35:29.849
Where are your experts
and panels on that?

35:43.600 --> 35:45.807
Another martini, dirty.

35:45.808 --> 35:47.974
Thank you.
Let me give you my card.
You can keep it open.

35:47.975 --> 35:50.683
Manager says
whatever you need,
it's on the house.

35:53.183 --> 35:56.515
What'd they do,

35:56.516 --> 35:57.765
if the drinks are on them

35:57.766 --> 36:00.349
because you've been
seriously wronged?

36:00.350 --> 36:04.515
Maybe they're just
rewarding me for being
a loyal customer.

36:04.516 --> 36:06.515
Nah.
Nah?

36:06.516 --> 36:09.140
Isn't the way the world works.

36:09.141 --> 36:11.515
Indeed it is not.
Heh heh!

36:11.516 --> 36:12.765
I'm sorry to interrupt.

36:12.766 --> 36:15.557
Would you mind
signing this for me?

36:15.558 --> 36:17.140
Oh, absolutely.

36:17.141 --> 36:19.182
Should I make it out to anyone?

36:19.183 --> 36:20.974
To Gail.
To Gail. Sure.

36:20.975 --> 36:22.891
Please.
No problem.

36:24.641 --> 36:26.182
God Bless.

36:26.183 --> 36:27.724
Heh heh! Thank you.

36:27.725 --> 36:29.683
Take care.

36:31.183 --> 36:32.432
What?

36:32.433 --> 36:34.099
I hear it's amazing,

36:34.100 --> 36:36.432
your book.

36:36.433 --> 36:38.432
Ah, the writing's
so-so.

36:38.433 --> 36:40.474
People respond to the idea.

36:40.475 --> 36:43.350
Why no question mark?

36:44.850 --> 36:47.057
"What's Next," period.

36:47.058 --> 36:49.849
I mean, no offense,
but it's not like
you know what's next.

36:49.850 --> 36:51.765
Exactly. No one knows.

36:51.766 --> 36:55.932
But we can't spend our lives
waiting around for something
that may never come.

36:55.933 --> 36:59.224
Back.

36:59.225 --> 37:00.682
Sorry?

37:00.683 --> 37:03.225
Something that may
never come back.

37:07.350 --> 37:10.807
You lost someone?

37:10.808 --> 37:13.225
I did.

37:16.308 --> 37:17.890
You know,
my daughter... ahem...

37:17.891 --> 37:20.682
about a year ago,
she was out in
our backyard,

37:20.683 --> 37:22.349
chasing around some
of her friends,

37:22.350 --> 37:25.890
and she was laughing.

37:25.891 --> 37:29.890
Then she saw me
watching her and she
looked guilty,

37:29.891 --> 37:33.141
like she wasn't sure
if it was OK
to be happy.

37:35.225 --> 37:38.890
But this, what we've
experienced...

37:38.891 --> 37:41.265
it isn't grief.

37:41.266 --> 37:43.766
It's never-ending.

37:45.266 --> 37:48.182
Ambiguous loss.

37:48.183 --> 37:52.890
If my 8-year-old can
find happiness within,

37:52.891 --> 37:55.433
why can't the rest of us?

37:59.141 --> 38:00.765
Bullshit.

38:00.766 --> 38:02.557
I'm sorry?

38:02.558 --> 38:04.390
No, you're not sorry.

38:04.391 --> 38:06.515
Sorry people don't write
fucking books.

38:06.516 --> 38:09.682
Wait a minute.
Ma'am, if I've offended you
in any way, that was not my...

38:09.683 --> 38:11.265
"Ambiguous loss"?

38:11.266 --> 38:14.224
What is ambiguous about
your family being gone?

38:14.225 --> 38:16.974
Well, and you
must know because
you lost what, 4?

38:16.975 --> 38:20.057
You count your parents
in that? What were they,
in their 70s?

38:20.058 --> 38:23.765
You sit there
and tell me a story
about your daughter.

38:23.766 --> 38:26.390
I lost everyone.

38:26.391 --> 38:30.849
I lost everything.
You fucking fraud!

38:30.850 --> 38:33.432
You fucking liar!
You're not in pain!

38:33.433 --> 38:36.849
Because if you were
in pain, you would know
there is no moving on!

38:36.850 --> 38:39.265
There is no happiness!
What's next?

38:39.266 --> 38:41.265
What's fucking next?!

38:41.266 --> 38:43.265
Nothing is next!

38:43.266 --> 38:45.391
Nothing!

39:12.016 --> 39:14.349
Evening.

39:18.975 --> 39:20.349
Excuse me.

39:20.350 --> 39:22.599
Excuse me. Excuse me.

39:22.600 --> 39:25.849
Miss, miss, miss.
I'm sorry to bother you.

39:25.850 --> 39:27.557
I saw you back in the bar
and I heard what you said.

39:27.558 --> 39:29.557
And I just wanted to ask you,

39:29.558 --> 39:31.640
do you want to feel this way?

39:31.641 --> 39:33.765
Yeah, I want to feel this way.

39:33.766 --> 39:34.974
Fuck off.

39:34.975 --> 39:37.932
You're right,
you know, about Johansen.

39:37.933 --> 39:40.099
What?
Excuse me.

39:40.100 --> 39:43.182
He's not in pain.
He's a fraud,
just like you said,

39:43.183 --> 39:45.058
and I can prove it.

39:48.141 --> 39:49.641
How?

40:24.516 --> 40:26.016
Come on.

41:13.183 --> 41:14.724
This is Ray.

41:14.725 --> 41:17.308
He'll take
your payment
information.

41:18.766 --> 41:20.682
Payment for what?

41:20.683 --> 41:21.890
Oh, last year Patrick Johansen,

41:21.891 --> 41:25.474
he walked
through doorways
just like that.

41:25.475 --> 41:28.350
If you want to know
what happened,
it's $1,000.

41:31.558 --> 41:34.390
What do you mean,
"what happened"?

41:34.391 --> 41:36.390
You on PayPal?

41:36.391 --> 41:39.225
If not, I can get you set up.

41:45.725 --> 41:47.682
I have an account.

41:47.683 --> 41:50.307
Go ahead and pull it up.

41:50.308 --> 41:52.808
You authorize the amount.

42:12.183 --> 42:13.432
Thank you.

42:13.433 --> 42:16.683
Now right this way.

42:18.183 --> 42:20.308
Go ahead.

42:22.975 --> 42:25.100
Come on.

42:44.933 --> 42:46.890
This is Wayne.

42:46.891 --> 42:48.766
Holy Wayne.

42:56.100 --> 42:58.682
Mmm, I don't think
she's heard of me.

42:58.683 --> 43:01.807
No, she's here
about Patrick Johansen.

43:01.808 --> 43:04.099
Who?

43:04.100 --> 43:07.307
The one who came to you
just before you left
for the ranch?

43:07.308 --> 43:10.849
Lost most of his family?

43:10.850 --> 43:13.349
He ended up
writing a book?
Oh, right.

43:13.350 --> 43:16.015
Right. I didn't read it.

43:16.016 --> 43:19.516
I assume he didn't mention me.

43:22.725 --> 43:25.266
Why would he mention you?

43:26.725 --> 43:30.058
Because I took
his pain from him.

43:38.391 --> 43:40.516
What are you doing?

43:41.891 --> 43:43.974
What's your name, love?

43:43.975 --> 43:47.349
Nora.
Nora.

43:47.350 --> 43:49.349
Nora, I don't give
a shit about you.

43:49.350 --> 43:52.724
I've already got your money,
and I'm fucking exhausted.

43:52.725 --> 43:54.808
You've lost someone, yes?

43:59.933 --> 44:01.725
Someones.

44:07.100 --> 44:11.266
And you believe
that you will always
feel that pain.

44:12.725 --> 44:16.349
And if it starts
to slip away, you...

44:16.350 --> 44:19.641
you seek it out
again, don't you?

44:21.350 --> 44:23.182
You won't let it kill you,

44:23.183 --> 44:26.557
but you won't...

44:26.558 --> 44:28.557
kill yourself.

44:31.808 --> 44:35.224
For whoever is joined
with all of the living,

44:35.225 --> 44:38.141
there is hope.

44:39.641 --> 44:40.849
Surely,

44:40.850 --> 44:44.766
a live dog is better
than a dead lion.

44:47.016 --> 44:48.016
Hope.

44:50.641 --> 44:53.182
It's your weakness.

44:53.183 --> 44:57.349
You want it gone
because you don't
deserve it.

45:03.100 --> 45:04.390
Nora...

45:04.391 --> 45:08.266
you do deserve hope.

45:13.766 --> 45:17.765
I've seen my own death,
and it's coming upon me
very soon,

45:17.766 --> 45:20.182
so this is
your one chance,
your only chance,

45:20.183 --> 45:23.557
and the question
remains the same.

45:23.558 --> 45:27.100
Do you want to feel this way?

45:30.058 --> 45:31.682
No.

45:31.683 --> 45:33.557
No.

45:40.141 --> 45:43.058
Then let me take it from you.

45:53.183 --> 45:54.641
Will I forget them?

45:57.933 --> 46:00.350
Never.

47:15.058 --> 47:17.015
You have a rewards card with us?

47:17.016 --> 47:19.140
Sure, I got it right here.

47:20.766 --> 47:22.140
Thanks.

47:22.141 --> 47:23.641
All right.

47:39.433 --> 47:41.432
Hello, you've
reached the Durst residence.
Please leave a message.

47:41.433 --> 47:44.849
